<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 8: TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER -
        FRONT COVER, FRONT HALF
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FRONT COVER, FRONT HALF</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="10">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>BE SURE OIL HAS BEEN DRAINED FROM THE ENGINE BEFORE REMOVING THE FRONT COVER.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Perform the following steps:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the serpentine belt and auto tensioner as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install breaker bar into belt tensioner and remove tension on belt</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove serpentine belt.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Return belt tensioner back to original position and remove breaker bar.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen mounting bolt and remove belt tensioner. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600804">8.4</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the alternator bracket as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the alternator</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and remove the alternator mounting bracket bolts. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600805">8.5</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the bracket.</para>
                    <figure id="ef1600804" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5077" filename="../figeg5/EG5077.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.4 Removing Auto Belt Tensioner</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600805" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5080" filename="../figeg5/EG5080.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.5 Removing Alternator Mounting Bracket</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fan drive hub and pulley as follows: Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600806">8.6</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using a special tool, purchased locally, remove bolts securing fan pulley to fan
                        drive. Remove pulley.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove fan hub drive capscrews and hub. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600807">8.7</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1600806" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5081" filename="../figeg5/EG5081.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.6 Removing Fan Drive Hub Pulley</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600807" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5084" filename="../figeg5/EG5084.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.7 Removing Fan Drive Hub</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Engines may be equipped with or without an air compressor or power steering pump.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the air compressor and or power steering pump (if equipped) as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two (2) bolts securing power steering pump to air compressor (if equipped).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen two (2) coolant hose clamps located at the air compressor and crankcase and
                        remove coolant hoses (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600808">8.8</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen two (2) nuts securing oil lubrication line to air compressor. Remove oil line
                        (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600809">8.9</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1600808" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5064" filename="../figeg5/EG5064.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.8 Loosen Coolant Hose Clamps</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600809" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6171" filename="../figeg6/EG6171.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.9 Loosen Oil Lubrication Line</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two (2) bolts securing air compressor bracket to air compressor. Remove
                        bracket (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600810">8.10</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two (2) bolts securing bracket to crankcase. Remove bracket (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600811">8.11</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two (2) bolts securing air compressor to front cover and remove air
                        compressor.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1600810" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5062" filename="../figeg5/EG5062.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.10 Removing Air Compressor Bracket Mounting Bolts</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600811" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6169" filename="../figeg6/EG6169.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.11 Removing Air Compressor To Crankcase Mounting Bolts</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the front cover as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Refer to Section 7,
                        <emph type="bold">"Vibration Damper, Crankshaft, Main Bearings, Flywheel and Crankcase"</emph>
                        for the removal of the engine front mounting bracket and vibration damper.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and remove all the front cover mounting bolts which secure the front cover
                        (front half) to the rear half of the front cover and crankcase. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600812">8.12</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lift the front half of the front cover (with hardware) from the rear half of the
                        front cover and set aside.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove gaskets and O-Rings from front cover and discard. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600813">8.13</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1600812" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5301" filename="../figeg5/EG5301.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.12 Front Cover Mounting Bolts</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600813" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg6905" filename="../figeg6/EG6905.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.13 Front Cover O-Ring And Gasket Locations</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">1. O-Rings</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">2. Crankcase Front Cover Reservoir Seal</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">3. Front Cover Oil Pressure Gasket</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">4. Front Cover Oil Suction Gasket</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>THE OIL PRESSURE RELIEF VALVE (STAMPED WITH AN "FC") SHOULD BE TAGGED UPON REMOVAL to
                                insure identification.
                                <emph type="underscr">DO NOT MIX</emph>
                                OIL PRESSURE RELIEF VALVE WITH OIL PRESSURE REGULATOR VALVE (FOUND IN SIDE OF
                                CRANKCASE).
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil pressure relief valve from front cover (rear half) and mark to identify its
                    location (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_218.xml" xrefid="ef1600814">8.14</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Valve may be removed by depressing plunger and trapping a length of copper wire when
                            released. Valve may then be removed by pulling the copper wire.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
